ce:section.ce:para:
1 g of CoCl₂·4H₂O, 2 g of FeCl₃·6H₂O, and 45 ml of deionized water were stirred at 70 °C for 120 min. Subsequently, 1.5 mol/L of NaOH solution was progressively added until a precipitate appeared. The obtained precipitate was meticulously cleaned with ethanol and distilled water to eliminate contaminants and subsequently dried. The aerated product was subsequently calcined at 500 °C in a muffle furnace for three hours. The black powder obtained is represented as CF-MNPs (
                        Scheme 2

                        ).
